# shadcn/ui Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- shadcn/ui is NOT a component library — it's copy-paste components you own
- Components live in `components/ui/` — you modify them directly
- Built on Radix UI primitives (accessible by default)
- Styled with Tailwind CSS + CSS variables for theming

## Installation
- Use `npx shadcn@latest add [component]` to add components
- Components are added to your codebase — you own and modify them
- Theme configuration in `globals.css` with CSS variables

## Best Practices
- DO: Customize components to match your design system
- DO: Use the `cn()` utility for conditional class merging
- DO: Compose complex UI from multiple shadcn components
- DO: Use `cva()` (class-variance-authority) for component variants
- DON'T: Install components you won't use
- DON'T: Override Radix accessibility features

## Theming
- Define theme in CSS variables: `--primary`, `--secondary`, `--destructive`
- Support dark mode with `.dark` class or `prefers-color-scheme`
- Use HSL color format for consistency

## Common Components
- `<Button variant="default|destructive|outline|ghost">` — Variants, not custom classes
- `<Dialog>` / `<Sheet>` — Modal + slide-over panels
- `<Command>` — Command palette (cmdk)
- `<Form>` — React Hook Form + Zod validation integration
- `<DataTable>` — TanStack Table integration
